---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Olle Rönn | Secure Homelab">
  <section class="hero homelab-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Project Case Study</p>

    <h1>Secure Homelab</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      Secure Homelab is a practical infrastructure and cybersecurity project where
      I built, secured and documented a small Linux-based server environment using
      Ubuntu Server, SSH key authentication, UFW, fail2ban, Docker, Portainer,
      Uptime Kuma, Homepage and Nginx.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a
        class="button"
        href="https://github.com/ollernn/secure-homelab"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
      >
        View GitHub
      </a>

      <a class="button secondary" href="/projects">
        Back to projects
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Status</p>
      <h2>Version 1 complete</h2>
      <p>
        The first version of the homelab is complete. The environment is installed,
        hardened, documented and running internal Docker-based services for
        management, monitoring and dashboard access.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="status-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Environment</span>
        <h3>Ubuntu Server VM</h3>
        <p>
          The server runs as a virtual machine in Oracle VirtualBox on a Windows
          host machine.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Security</span>
        <h3>Hardened access</h3>
        <p>
          SSH was hardened with key-based authentication, disabled root login and
          disabled password authentication.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Services</span>
        <h3>Docker-based services</h3>
        <p>
          Portainer, Uptime Kuma, Homepage and Nginx are running as internal
          Docker services.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Purpose</p>
      <h2>Why I built this project</h2>
      <p>
        The purpose of Secure Homelab v1 was to create a practical learning
        environment for Linux administration, server hardening, secure remote
        access, Docker, monitoring and technical documentation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="purpose-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">01</span>
        <h3>Build practical infrastructure skills</h3>
        <p>
          I wanted to go beyond theory and build a real server environment where
          I could install, configure, secure and troubleshoot services myself.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">02</span>
        <h3>Apply security from the start</h3>
        <p>
          The project focuses on secure SSH access, firewall rules, fail2ban,
          internal-only services and careful documentation without exposing secrets.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">03</span>
        <h3>Document the full process</h3>
        <p>
          The goal was not only to build the environment, but also to document
          decisions, problems, fixes and lessons learned in a clear GitHub structure.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Architecture</p>
      <h2>Final version 1 architecture</h2>
      <p>
        The environment runs locally in VirtualBox and uses Docker to host internal
        services on a shared Docker network.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="architecture-card">
      <pre><code>Windows Host PC
   |
Oracle VirtualBox
   |
Ubuntu Server 26.04 LTS VM
   |
Security Layer
   |-- SSH key authentication
   |-- UFW firewall
   |-- fail2ban
   |
Docker Engine
   |
Shared Docker Network: homelab
   |-- Portainer
   |-- Uptime Kuma
   |-- Homepage
   |-- Nginx</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Environment</p>
      <h2>Virtual machine setup</h2>
      <p>
        The homelab was built as a local virtual server environment using Ubuntu
        Server inside Oracle VirtualBox.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="spec-grid">
      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>OS</span>
        <strong>Ubuntu Server 26.04 LTS</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>Virtualization</span>
        <strong>Oracle VirtualBox</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>RAM</span>
        <strong>4096 MB</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>CPU</span>
        <strong>2 cores</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>Disk</span>
        <strong>80 GB</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>Network mode</span>
        <strong>NAT</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>Hostname</span>
        <strong>secure-homelab</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="spec-item">
        <span>Local user</span>
        <strong>olle</strong>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Security</p>
      <h2>Security configuration</h2>
      <p>
        The server was hardened by securing SSH access, enabling a firewall and
        using fail2ban to protect against repeated failed login attempts.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="security-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">SSH</span>
        <h3>Key-based authentication</h3>
        <p>
          SSH keys were created on Windows and used to authenticate securely to
          the Ubuntu server.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Hardening</span>
        <h3>Root and password login disabled</h3>
        <p>
          Root login and password authentication were disabled to reduce the risk
          of unauthorized access.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Firewall</span>
        <h3>UFW enabled</h3>
        <p>
          UFW was configured to allow only the required ports for SSH and internal
          homelab services.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="tag">Protection</span>
        <h3>fail2ban installed</h3>
        <p>
          fail2ban was installed and verified to add basic protection against
          repeated failed SSH login attempts.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Docker Services</p>
      <h2>Services running in version 1</h2>
      <p>
        Docker and Docker Compose were installed and verified. The homelab uses a
        shared Docker network so services can communicate internally by container name.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="service-list">
      <article class="service-item">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Docker management</span>
          <h3>Portainer</h3>
        </div>

        <p>
          Used as a graphical interface for managing Docker containers, volumes
          and the local Docker environment.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="service-item">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Monitoring</span>
          <h3>Uptime Kuma</h3>
        </div>

        <p>
          Used to monitor internal services such as Portainer, Homepage and Nginx.
          All monitored services were verified as up.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="service-item">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Dashboard</span>
          <h3>Homepage</h3>
        </div>

        <p>
          Used as an internal homelab dashboard with links to Portainer, Uptime
          Kuma and Nginx.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="service-item">
        <div>
          <span class="tag">Web server</span>
          <h3>Nginx</h3>
        </div>

        <p>
          Used as a basic test web server to verify Docker networking, port
          mappings and service monitoring.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Networking</p>
      <h2>Networking and port forwarding</h2>
      <p>
        Because the VM runs behind VirtualBox NAT, port forwarding is used from
        the Windows host to the Ubuntu VM.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="port-grid">
      <article class="port-item">
        <span>127.0.0.1:2222</span>
        <strong>SSH</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="port-item">
        <span>127.0.0.1:9443</span>
        <strong>Portainer</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="port-item">
        <span>127.0.0.1:3001</span>
        <strong>Uptime Kuma</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="port-item">
        <span>127.0.0.1:3000</span>
        <strong>Homepage</strong>
      </article>

      <article class="port-item">
        <span>127.0.0.1:8080</span>
        <strong>Nginx</strong>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="note-card">
      <h3>Important networking lesson</h3>
      <p>
        One key lesson was that <code>127.0.0.1</code> inside a Docker container
        refers to the container itself, not the Windows host or another container.
        To monitor internal services correctly, Uptime Kuma was configured to use
        Docker container names such as <code>portainer</code>, <code>homepage</code>
        and <code>nginx</code>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Problems solved</p>
      <h2>Technical problems I solved</h2>
      <p>
        Several issues came up during the build. These were documented and fixed
        as part of the project.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="problem-list">
      <article class="problem-item">
        <span>01</span>
        <div>
          <h3>SSH timeout through VirtualBox NAT</h3>
          <p>
            SSH to the VM IP address timed out because NAT did not expose the SSH
            port directly. I solved this with port forwarding from
            <code>127.0.0.1:2222</code> to port <code>22</code> on the VM.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="problem-item">
        <span>02</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Password authentication did not disable correctly</h3>
          <p>
            The setting was overridden by a cloud-init SSH configuration file. I
            updated the relevant configuration and verified the final SSH settings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="problem-item">
        <span>03</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Container monitoring with localhost failed</h3>
          <p>
            Uptime Kuma could not monitor services through <code>127.0.0.1</code>
            from inside its container. I solved this by creating a shared Docker
            network and using container names for internal monitoring.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="problem-item">
        <span>04</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Portainer self-signed certificate</h3>
          <p>
            Portainer uses a self-signed certificate in this local setup. For the
            internal Uptime Kuma monitor, TLS/SSL certificate errors were ignored.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Documentation</p>
      <h2>GitHub documentation</h2>
      <p>
        The project was documented in a structured GitHub repository with separate
        files for overview, VM setup, networking, installation, security, Docker
        services, lessons learned and a final version 1 summary.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="documentation-card">
      <div>
        <h3>Repository structure</h3>
        <p>
          The documentation includes Markdown files, Docker configuration folders,
          architecture diagrams and screenshots.
        </p>
      </div>

      <a
        class="button secondary"
        href="https://github.com/ollernn/secure-homelab"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer"
      >
        Open GitHub repository
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Lessons learned</p>
      <h2>What I learned</h2>
      <p>
        The project gave me practical experience in building, securing,
        troubleshooting and documenting a small server environment from start to
        finished version 1.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="learning-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Linux server administration</h3>
        <p>
          Installing Ubuntu Server, updating packages, installing tools, checking
          services and working without a graphical interface.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Secure remote access</h3>
        <p>
          Configuring SSH keys, disabling insecure login methods and verifying
          the final SSH configuration.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Docker operations</h3>
        <p>
          Running services in containers, creating volumes, using Docker Compose
          and connecting services through a shared Docker network.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Monitoring and troubleshooting</h3>
        <p>
          Setting up service monitoring, understanding container networking and
          solving real issues during the build.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="next-section">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">Future improvements</p>
      <h2>Possible version 2 improvements</h2>
      <p>
        Version 1 is complete, but the homelab can be extended further with more
        security, automation, logging and cloud integration.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="next-list">
      <span>Reverse proxy</span>
      <span>HTTPS for internal services</span>
      <span>Centralized logging</span>
      <span>Grafana dashboards</span>
      <span>Automated backups</span>
      <span>Azure integration</span>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .homelab-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.2vw, 4.2rem);
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .status-grid,
  .purpose-grid,
  .security-grid,
  .learning-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .security-grid,
  .learning-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .architecture-card,
  .note-card,
  .documentation-card,
  .next-section {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015)),
      var(--surface);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
  }

  .architecture-card {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.35rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  pre {
    margin: 0;
    white-space: pre;
  }

  pre code {
    display: block;
    color: var(--text-soft);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .spec-grid,
  .port-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .spec-item,
.port-item {
  padding: 1.2rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  background:
    linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015)),
    var(--surface);
  transition:
    transform 160ms ease,
    border-color 160ms ease,
    background 160ms ease;
}

.spec-item:hover,
.port-item:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background:
    linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
    var(--surface-soft);
}

  .spec-item span,
  .port-item span {
    display: block;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .spec-item strong,
  .port-item strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .service-list,
  .problem-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .service-item,
  .problem-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(220px, 0.7fr) minmax(0, 1.3fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.2rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015)),
      var(--surface);
    transition:
      transform 160ms ease,
      border-color 160ms ease,
      background 160ms ease;
  }

  .problem-item {
    grid-template-columns: 52px 1fr;
  }

  .service-item:hover,
  .problem-item:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
      var(--surface-soft);
  }

  .service-item h3,
  .problem-item h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .service-item p,
  .problem-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .problem-item > span {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 850;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .note-card {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .note-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background:
    linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
    var(--surface-soft);
}

  .note-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  code {
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.14);
    padding: 0.08rem 0.28rem;
    border-radius: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.9em;
  }

  .documentation-card {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.35rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .documentation-card {
  transition:
    transform 160ms ease,
    border-color 160ms ease,
    background 160ms ease;
}

.documentation-card:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background:
    linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
    var(--surface-soft);
}

  .documentation-card p {
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .next-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(280px, 0.9fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .next-section:hover {
  transform: translateY(-2px);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background:
    linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.045), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02)),
    var(--surface-soft);
}

  .next-section p {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .next-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }

  .next-list span {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  width: fit-content;
  padding: 0.34rem 0.7rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: 999px;
  color: var(--text-soft);
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.025);
  font-size: 0.82rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  transition:
    color 160ms ease,
    border-color 160ms ease,
    background 160ms ease,
    transform 160ms ease;
}

.next-list span:hover {
  color: var(--accent);
  border-color: var(--border-hover);
  background: rgba(147, 197, 253, 0.08);
  transform: translateY(-1px);
}

  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    .status-grid,
    .purpose-grid,
    .security-grid,
    .learning-grid,
    .spec-grid,
    .port-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    }

    .documentation-card,
    .next-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .status-grid,
    .purpose-grid,
    .security-grid,
    .learning-grid,
    .spec-grid,
    .port-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .service-item,
    .problem-item {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>